and I don't want to like take away from the festivities.

479
00:27:23,919 --> 00:27:26,720
Well, we'll get all our sustenance in maybe

480
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:28,319
and then we can go check it out.

481
00:27:28,319 --> 00:27:29,599
Chicken flies across the table.

482
00:27:30,879 --> 00:27:31,919
While this is happening,

483
00:27:32,639 --> 00:27:34,639
I pull on Bazaar's cloak

484
00:27:35,200 --> 00:27:38,640
and I like gesture them to lean down a little bit

485
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:40,960
and as they're having their conversation.

486
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:44,720
Do they know that they can just get books

487
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:47,200
from like stores and stuff

488
00:27:47,840 --> 00:27:50,880
and that they probably shouldn't cook them

489
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:53,840
because it's paper?

490
00:27:53,840 --> 00:27:56,160
That will be another lesson that we will cover.

491
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:59,920
In fact, you may learn about it tonight

492
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:01,759
depending on how things go,

493
00:28:01,759 --> 00:28:06,079
but I don't even know where to begin with this one,

494
00:28:06,079 --> 00:28:08,400
but you are correct in what you are saying.

495
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:09,839
That sounds logical to me,

496
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:11,839
but there's a lot of things

497
00:28:11,839 --> 00:28:14,240
that you got to read between the lines in those books.

498
00:28:15,279 --> 00:28:16,960
Shit, I think I'm just confusing it.

499
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:21,440
I didn't go to school, Bazaar.

500
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:24,079
Well, school is fun,

501
00:28:24,079 --> 00:28:26,319
but sometimes it's expensive to learn things

502
00:28:26,319 --> 00:28:28,879
and when you can just learn them from people

503
00:28:28,879 --> 00:28:30,559
that you happen to be around

504
00:28:30,559 --> 00:28:31,599
and that's what we're doing here.

505
00:28:32,560 --> 00:28:33,440
You don't know what they're talking about.

506
00:28:33,440 --> 00:28:37,440
Kavlarananne is going to teach me how to cook books?

507
00:28:37,440 --> 00:28:39,040
I don't think it's going to be a teaching thing

508
00:28:39,040 --> 00:28:40,240
as much as it is going to be

509
00:28:40,240 --> 00:28:41,920
just a learning opportunity

510
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:45,040
through observation and experience.

511
00:28:45,920 --> 00:28:56,160
I'm going to observe Bonwyn stealing raw books.

512
00:28:57,440 --> 00:28:58,400
That's to be seen,

513
00:28:58,400 --> 00:29:00,240
but that's the goal, it sounds like.

514
00:29:01,039 --> 00:29:01,920
Oh, can I come?

515
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:04,880
Well, I mean, if we're invited,

516
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:07,519
I mean, if it is at a hall in the city

517
00:29:07,519 --> 00:29:10,079
as I kind of look over at them with a glare,

518
00:29:10,079 --> 00:29:13,359
like pretty obvious, but you know.

519
00:29:13,359 --> 00:29:15,680
Really sneaky, really sneaky language

520
00:29:15,680 --> 00:29:17,359
between me and Kav over here.

521
00:29:17,359 --> 00:29:19,440
But, you know, if there's, you know,

522
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:21,599
I know Kavlarananne's been doing some work up there,

523
00:29:21,599 --> 00:29:24,319
but if there's more credence needed

524
00:29:24,319 --> 00:29:25,920
to be given to a visit,

525
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:29,120
then who better than a mayor's advisor?

526
00:29:29,120 --> 00:29:30,400
Do you have an office, Kavlarananne?

527
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:31,120
Can I see it?

528
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:36,480
I've never been inside of town hall before.

529
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:38,160
Like, maybe could I have a tour?

530
00:29:39,120 --> 00:29:41,520
I could probably arrange for a tour.

531
00:29:41,520 --> 00:29:44,000
I share an office, so it's not my office,

532
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:45,360
but you remember.

533
00:29:45,360 --> 00:29:46,400
Like bunk beds.

534
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:47,120
Yeah, you remember.

535
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:50,240
Once I stacked a crate on top of another crate

536
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:53,440
and then Tally slept under that first crate inside

537
00:29:53,440 --> 00:29:54,640
and then I slept on the top.

538
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:54,960
You know what?

539
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:56,560
That's very creative.

540
00:29:56,560 --> 00:29:57,040
Thank you.

541
00:29:57,920 --> 00:30:00,000
So can I see your office bunk beds?

542
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,200
Well, there's no beds,

543
00:30:01,759 --> 00:30:03,839
but in fact there's only just the one desk.

544
00:30:04,559 --> 00:30:05,839
But we make it work.

545
00:30:05,839 --> 00:30:07,519
You know, he's really good at the...

546
00:30:08,319 --> 00:30:09,200
Anyway, doesn't matter.

547
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:11,440
Yes, we'll go and we'll get a tour.

548
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:16,480
I wonder if Nina's good friend,

549
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:20,240
Bizard, couldn't maybe wrangle her

550
00:30:20,240 --> 00:30:23,039
as a high-ranking sort of official

551
00:30:23,039 --> 00:30:26,879
into giving a personalized tour

552
00:30:26,879 --> 00:30:30,559
to his promising new apprentice, student,

553
00:30:30,559 --> 00:30:32,799
however you want to spin that and just...

554
00:30:32,799 --> 00:30:33,599
Protégé.

555
00:30:33,599 --> 00:30:34,639
I think that's what, right?

556
00:30:35,759 --> 00:30:37,440
Protégé, absolutely.

557
00:30:37,440 --> 00:30:39,519
That's a very big word for somebody

558
00:30:39,519 --> 00:30:40,559
who didn't go to school.

559
00:30:41,119 --> 00:30:41,920
Did I say that word?

560
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,119
I don't know how to spell it.

561
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:44,399
Did I say that?

562
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:45,599
Maybe I did.

563
00:30:46,960 --> 00:30:48,559
As far as asking Nina goes,

564
00:30:51,119 --> 00:30:52,319
I certainly could ask Nina.

565
00:30:52,319 --> 00:30:56,480
I mean, I wouldn't say that we're like friends.

566
00:30:57,200 --> 00:30:58,240
I mean, we work together

567
00:30:58,799 --> 00:31:02,720
and that's about as far as that relationship goes.

568
00:31:02,720 --> 00:31:05,519
I feel like it might not even be that close.

569
00:31:07,039 --> 00:31:10,159
Does she have the rob-ups?

570
00:31:10,159 --> 00:31:11,279
You're getting closer.

571
00:31:11,279 --> 00:31:12,399
You're getting really close.

572
00:31:13,599 --> 00:31:15,039
Maybe you don't want her there

573
00:31:15,759 --> 00:31:17,279
if you're going to take her things.

574
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:20,799
I never take ever,

575
00:31:20,879 --> 00:31:22,079
but if I were going to,

576
00:31:22,879 --> 00:31:24,720
it wouldn't be when that person was there,

577
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:26,399
which I wouldn't.

578
00:31:27,119 --> 00:31:28,639
Yeah, hypothetically,

579
00:31:28,639 --> 00:31:29,919
it would not make any sense

580
00:31:29,919 --> 00:31:32,079
to take something from someone when they're there.

581
00:31:32,720 --> 00:31:36,639
But would it be the perfect opportunity?

582
00:31:37,359 --> 00:31:40,240
Well, what if that person was there

583
00:31:41,279 --> 00:31:42,720
without being there

584
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:44,399
and it just looked like them?

585
00:31:45,039 --> 00:31:46,879
Okay, say more.

586
00:31:46,879 --> 00:31:48,480
I'm going to need to hear more about this.

587
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,799
Bizarre pulls out his tome

588
00:31:50,799 --> 00:31:52,079
and he starts flipping through it

589
00:31:52,079 --> 00:31:52,799
and he's like,

590
00:31:52,799 --> 00:31:53,759
this page right here.

591
00:31:54,319 --> 00:31:58,319
I could make myself look like Nina.

592
00:31:58,319 --> 00:31:58,819
What?

593
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:01,920
I've seen Nina.

594
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,759
She's half your size.

595
00:32:03,759 --> 00:32:04,259
She's...

596
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:07,120
You know, there's some adjustment

597
00:32:07,839 --> 00:32:10,799
that's allowed within the confines of the spell,

598
00:32:10,799 --> 00:32:13,920
but I think it could potentially work.

599
00:32:14,720 --> 00:32:15,920
And, you know,

600
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:20,800
it would give us a lot of ammo against the mayor

601
00:32:20,800 --> 00:32:22,400
and against, you know,

602
00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:25,120
most of the rest of the group

603
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:28,320
that's involved with their ne'er-do-willing

604
00:32:28,320 --> 00:32:29,120
against the city.

605
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:30,800
It's a gamble, though.

606
00:32:31,840 --> 00:32:33,200
Caviar, the expert.

607
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:36,080
Would it be helpful to have someone...

608
00:32:36,880 --> 00:32:38,960
You're blowing my mind, Bizarre.

609
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:42,080
But they could look like someone

610
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:45,440
where we were trying to find the books.

611
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:49,120
That seems like that would be amazing, right?

612
00:32:49,120 --> 00:32:50,559
Yeah, I mean, it really could be.

613
00:32:51,120 --> 00:32:52,799
Now, when you say look like,

614
00:32:52,799 --> 00:32:54,720
does that also include sound like?

615
00:32:56,480 --> 00:32:59,039
Reading over the text real quick,

616
00:32:59,039 --> 00:33:02,320
because it's not something I've really thought about using,

617
00:33:02,320 --> 00:33:05,039
but it's one I could certainly be prepared to use.

618
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:09,279
What does she sound like?

619
00:33:09,279 --> 00:33:10,160
Does she sound different?

620
00:33:11,840 --> 00:33:13,920
Would he just have to talk a little higher?

621
00:33:14,560 --> 00:33:21,440
Well, I mean, not as comical, I guess, as that,

622
00:33:21,440 --> 00:33:22,800
but, you know, just...

623
00:33:23,920 --> 00:33:27,440
Could you sound like her if the need arose?

624
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:31,279
Or could you convincingly pretend

625
00:33:31,279 --> 00:33:33,840
you had a really sore throat and just couldn't talk?

626
00:33:33,840 --> 00:33:34,800
Now, that I think I could do.

627
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,240
Yeah, that I think I could do.

628
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:40,480
As far as I can see,

629
00:33:40,559 --> 00:33:44,480
the, you know, clothing, armor, weapons, those kind of things.

630
00:33:45,200 --> 00:33:50,400
Yeah, I can make myself at least a foot shorter or taller, so...

631
00:33:51,039 --> 00:33:52,960
I mean, definitely shorter in this case.

632
00:33:53,920 --> 00:33:55,599
I would have to fake a voice.

633
00:33:55,599 --> 00:33:56,799
And if anybody were to...

634
00:33:58,160 --> 00:34:00,960
I don't know, I can't touch anybody that doesn't know,

635
00:34:00,960 --> 00:34:02,319
because otherwise then it's like,

636
00:34:02,319 --> 00:34:05,440
ha ha, obviously you're not that short.

637
00:34:05,440 --> 00:34:07,680
So there's a lot of potential holes in it,

638
00:34:07,680 --> 00:34:09,200
not to mention it is a...

639
00:34:10,240 --> 00:34:13,200
Yeah, it's not the most taxing illusion,

640
00:34:13,200 --> 00:34:18,639
but, you know, still have to expend the life essence for it.

641
00:34:18,639 --> 00:34:20,159
Sure, gotta pay the tax, yeah.

642
00:34:20,159 --> 00:34:21,119
Yeah, exactly.

643
00:34:21,119 --> 00:34:23,440
Very, very appropriate, Kavlaranan.

644
00:34:23,440 --> 00:34:25,200
We got a lot of wings to eat still,

645
00:34:25,200 --> 00:34:26,559
so let's just keep discussing.

646
00:34:26,559 --> 00:34:28,400
I'm sure we can hammer something out.

647
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:29,760
Oh, yeah, absolutely.

648
00:34:29,760 --> 00:34:30,800
Snarf, snarf, snarf.

649
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:34,720
You're gonna have boobs.

